{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MydggoJedxdECYacbvspFF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the issue:\n\n1. The StatefulSet has 3 replicas but only 1 pod is running and it's not Ready.\n2. The probes are using `mongosh --eval \"db.adminCommand('ping')\" --quiet` without authentication credentials.\n3. Since auth is enabled (`--auth` flag and keyFile), the `mongosh` ping command needs credentials to work.\n4. The probes have very aggressive settings:\n   - `failureThreshold: 2` (too low)\n   - `initialDelaySeconds: 5/15` (too short for MongoDB startup with auth)\n   - `timeoutSeconds: 1` (too short for mongosh to connect and authenticate)\n\nThe fix requires adding authentication credentials to the probe commands, increasing the timeout to give mongosh enough time to authenticate, and raising both the initial delay and failure threshold to allow MongoDB to start properly. I need to check the secrets for the admin credentials and examine the mongod config file to understand the current setup.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2093,"cache_read_input_tokens":28324,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2093},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2208e562-ed9b-4743-9e4f-56b62c256165","uuid":"6b220187-b428-40a9-95bb-9b2dfe26d402","request_id":"req_011CcgdQ4LcFMhcPwiMLW2U8"}
