{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QsH224Fuha3uDdm7U8rT8o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issues clearly:\n\n1. `timeoutSeconds: 1` is too short - the probe is timing out (last event: \"timed out after 1s\")\n2. `failureThreshold: 2` is too low - MongoDB needs time to start up\n3. The probe doesn't use authentication credentials - when auth is enabled, `mongosh` without credentials might not connect properly (though `db.adminCommand('ping')` should actually work without auth in some cases)\n4. `initialDelaySeconds: 5/15` might be too short\n5. The real issue is that the timeout is killing the probe before mongosh can even establish a connection - I need to bump that to at least 5-10 seconds, increase the initial delay for liveness to around 30 seconds to give MongoDB proper startup time, and raise the failure threshold to be more forgiving before the pod gets terminated.\n\nFor the authentication-enabled setup, the probe command should include the health user credentials so it can actually authenticate and run the ping command successfully.\n\nActually, wait - the `ping` command in MongoDB doesn't require authentication even when auth is enabled, so the real bottleneck is just the timeout being too short. Let me adjust the probe settings more aggressively: increasing `timeoutSeconds` to 5 seconds, pushing `initialDelaySeconds` to 30 for liveness and 15 for readiness, and bumping both `failureThreshold` values up to 6 to give the pod more breathing room before it gets killed.\n\nI should verify whether the health user actually exists in MongoDB yet, since the database just started and the replica set initialization might not have completed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1362,"cache_read_input_tokens":31428,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1362},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2208e562-ed9b-4743-9e4f-56b62c256165","uuid":"d541194b-3ecd-4e61-9ed9-a5519e7d0712","request_id":"req_011CcgdR3eDU9EaCFWBNC4uU"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QsH224Fuha3uDdm7U8rT8o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The root causes are clear:\n1. `timeoutSeconds: 1` is too short — mongosh takes >1s to connect (last event shows explicit timeout)\n2. `failureThreshold: 2` is too low — pods get killed before MongoDB finishes starting\n3. `initialDelaySeconds` too short for liveness (15s) and readiness (5s)\n\nLet me patch the probes:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1362,"cache_read_input_tokens":31428,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1362},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2208e562-ed9b-4743-9e4f-56b62c256165","uuid":"bcc0f451-e93f-492a-9f83-6da5a3e4e317","request_id":"req_011CcgdR3eDU9EaCFWBNC4uU"}
